In [[category theory]], a [[functor]] 

:<math>F:C\to D</math> 

is '''essentially surjective''' (or '''dense''') if each object <math>d</math> of <math>D</math> is isomorphic to an object of the form <math>Fc</math> for some object <math>c</math> of <math>C</math>. Any functor which is part of an [[Equivalence of categories|equivalence]] is essentially surjective.

